sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client
    participant Gateway as MaaS Gateway<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS Terminate
    participant BBR as payload-processing (BBR)<br/>9004/TCP gRPC TLS SIMPLE
    participant Authorino as Authorino<br/>Auth Engine
    participant MaaSAPI as maas-api<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Limitador as Limitador<br/>Rate Limiter
    participant KServe as KServe InferenceService<br/>HTTPS
    participant ExtProvider as External LLM Provider<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant PostgreSQL as PostgreSQL<br/>5432/TCP
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    Note over Client,ExtProvider: Flow 1: User Inference Request (API Key Auth)

    Client->>Gateway: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>Auth: Bearer sk-oai-*
    Gateway->>BBR: ext-proc: extract model name<br/>gRPC/9004 TLS SIMPLE
    BBR-->>Gateway: X-Gateway-Model-Name header
    Gateway->>Authorino: Authenticate request
    Authorino->>MaaSAPI: POST /internal/v1/api-keys/validate<br/>HTTPS/8443 (NetworkPolicy)
    MaaSAPI->>PostgreSQL: SELECT api_key<br/>SHA-256 hash lookup
    PostgreSQL-->>MaaSAPI: Key record + groups snapshot
    MaaSAPI-->>Authorino: 200 OK (user identity)
    Authorino->>MaaSAPI: POST /internal/v1/subscriptions/select<br/>HTTPS/8443 (NetworkPolicy)
    MaaSAPI-->>Authorino: Selected subscription + rate limits
    Authorino-->>Gateway: Auth success + identity context
    Gateway->>Limitador: Check token rate limit<br/>per user/subscription
    Limitador-->>Gateway: Allowed
    Gateway->>KServe: Forward inference request<br/>mTLS (auth header stripped)
    KServe-->>Gateway: Inference response
    Gateway-->>Client: JSON Response

    Note over Client,ExtProvider: Flow 2: ExternalModel Routing

    Client->>Gateway: POST /{ns}/{model}/v1/chat/completions<br/>Auth: Bearer token
    Gateway->>BBR: ext-proc: resolve provider<br/>gRPC/9004 TLS SIMPLE
    BBR->>K8sAPI: GET ExternalModel, Secret<br/>HTTPS/443 SA token
    K8sAPI-->>BBR: Provider config + credentials
    BBR-->>Gateway: Translated request + injected API key<br/>+ upstream host
    Gateway->>Authorino: Authenticate + authorize
    Authorino-->>Gateway: Auth success
    Gateway->>Limitador: Check token rate limit
    Limitador-->>Gateway: Allowed
    Gateway->>ExtProvider: Forward request<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS SIMPLE<br/>Provider API key injected
    ExtProvider-->>Gateway: LLM response
    Gateway->>BBR: ext-proc: translate response
    BBR-->>Gateway: Translated response
    Gateway-->>Client: Unified JSON response

    Note over Client,ExtProvider: Flow 3: API Key Management

    Client->>Gateway: POST /v1/api-keys<br/>Auth: OpenShift Bearer token
    Gateway->>Authorino: Authenticate (kubernetesTokenReview)
    Authorino->>K8sAPI: TokenReview<br/>HTTPS/443
    K8sAPI-->>Authorino: User identity + groups
    Authorino-->>Gateway: Auth success + headers
    Gateway->>MaaSAPI: POST /v1/api-keys<br/>X-MaaS-Username/Group headers
    MaaSAPI->>K8sAPI: SubjectAccessReview<br/>HTTPS/443 SA token
    K8sAPI-->>MaaSAPI: Authorized
    MaaSAPI->>PostgreSQL: INSERT api_key<br/>(SHA-256 hashed)
    PostgreSQL-->>MaaSAPI: Created
    MaaSAPI-->>Gateway: 201 + plaintext key (shown once)
    Gateway-->>Client: API Key response

    Note over Client,ExtProvider: Flow 4: Tenant Platform Reconciliation

    Note right of K8sAPI: maas-controller watches Tenant CR
    K8sAPI->>K8sAPI: Tenant CR created/updated
    Note right of K8sAPI: maas-controller reconciles
    K8sAPI->>K8sAPI: Kustomize render (in-process)
    K8sAPI->>K8sAPI: Server-Side Apply manifests<br/>(maas-api, BBR, policies)
    K8sAPI->>K8sAPI: Check Deployment readiness
    K8sAPI->>K8sAPI: Update Tenant status conditions
